WEBVTT

00:14.180 --> 00:15.348
From now on,

00:16.599 --> 00:18.226
can I do as I please?

00:27.527 --> 00:29.821
Well, I…

00:29.904 --> 00:32.657
What are you two doing over there?
Come in, Kyeong-nam!

00:35.702 --> 00:36.786
Let's go inside.

00:41.624 --> 00:43.877
How could you not remember what you drew?

00:43.960 --> 00:46.504
Episode 17, Si-woo and Na-ra's first kiss.

00:46.588 --> 00:49.466
Ms. Jang comes over and slaps her.
Don't you remember?

00:49.549 --> 00:52.302
Why do you have my work memorized?
That's creepy.

00:52.385 --> 00:54.471
I hate it so much that I can't look away.

00:54.554 --> 00:56.848
You're dissing my work, aren't you?

00:56.931 --> 00:58.099
You can't even draw.

00:58.183 --> 01:01.394
Being an author
is not only about drawing well.

01:01.478 --> 01:04.773
It's about diligence and originality.
Just memorize that.

01:04.856 --> 01:08.151
Hey, anyone can talk about diligence,
but not you.

01:08.234 --> 01:11.988
I heard that Park and Seo here
are working overtime every Friday.

01:13.907 --> 01:15.950
Aren't I the only author on Fridays?

01:16.034 --> 01:17.702
I always send in my work early.

01:18.578 --> 01:19.412
Yeah…

01:21.873 --> 01:22.957
The thing is…

01:23.041 --> 01:26.836
He must be working late all the time
because your files are a mess.

01:26.920 --> 01:27.962
No, they're not.

01:28.046 --> 01:30.507
I do have rather high standards, so…

01:30.590 --> 01:32.592
-Huh?
-That's why.

01:34.135 --> 01:37.138
I bet you want to work with someone
who can actually draw, right?

01:37.847 --> 01:39.808
But I think he draws well.

01:40.391 --> 01:41.559
What? Who draws well?

01:41.643 --> 01:45.730
That piece. Wasn't it done by you?

01:47.398 --> 01:49.984
What? Was that how you originally drew?

01:50.068 --> 01:52.195
That's not my work.

01:52.278 --> 01:55.824
Right? I knew it was so good.
Who's the artist?

01:56.991 --> 01:58.618
-This guy.
-Huh?

02:01.037 --> 02:03.331
He gave it to me
when I moved into this studio.

02:03.414 --> 02:05.291
Whoa, how are you so good?

02:05.375 --> 02:07.043
You guys didn't know?

02:07.627 --> 02:10.672
Kyeong-nam was my art instructor
when I was preparing for college.

02:10.755 --> 02:11.589
Really?

02:11.673 --> 02:15.301
Well, it was just a part-time gig
when I was in college.

02:15.969 --> 02:17.929
You should do this for a living.

02:18.012 --> 02:19.139
Such a waste of talent.

02:19.222 --> 02:20.473
Right?

02:21.141 --> 02:23.560
See? Others see things the way I do.

02:23.643 --> 02:24.936
Stop.

02:25.019 --> 02:26.688
Plenty of people can draw like me.

02:26.771 --> 02:28.606
Come on. That's not true.

02:30.692 --> 02:32.193
Just worry about yourself.

02:32.277 --> 02:33.611
I'll handle it myself.

02:35.363 --> 02:37.365
This is the next episode.

02:37.907 --> 02:38.741
If I do this,

02:39.909 --> 02:41.578
don't you think it would be good?

02:41.661 --> 02:43.079
-It's nice.
-Right?

02:50.503 --> 02:52.672
Hwany, can I use your charger?

02:52.755 --> 02:55.341
There's one next to the sofa. Yes.

03:14.277 --> 03:15.486
Is he asleep?

03:16.362 --> 03:19.532
From now on, can I do as I please?

03:20.033 --> 03:22.118
What did he even mean by that?

03:34.255 --> 03:35.256
Are you doing okay?

03:35.340 --> 03:38.176
What? What do you mean?

03:38.885 --> 03:39.719
That.

03:41.346 --> 03:42.347
"That"?

03:58.529 --> 03:59.364
This.

04:07.413 --> 04:08.831
It's gotten a lot better.

04:14.003 --> 04:15.171
I'm screwed.

04:21.719 --> 04:23.638
EPISODE 8
THE ODD OR EVEN GAME

04:34.857 --> 04:35.942
Are you doing okay?

04:36.025 --> 04:37.193
Damn it!

04:40.154 --> 04:41.030
I miss you.

04:44.200 --> 04:45.285
From now on,

04:45.785 --> 04:47.662
can I do as I please?

04:49.914 --> 04:51.457
Let's go!

05:05.054 --> 05:06.055
Hello?

05:06.139 --> 05:08.391
Hey, where are you?
I'm near your place right now.

05:08.474 --> 05:09.976
What are you doing here?

05:10.643 --> 05:12.979
I was feeling down, so I went for a run.

05:13.062 --> 05:13.980
In this weather?

05:14.063 --> 05:16.733
Can I come over?
I even bought some bungeo-ppang.

05:16.816 --> 05:19.777
You should have told me sooner!
I'm at the department store.

05:19.861 --> 05:20.695
Huh?

05:21.738 --> 05:22.822
You're shopping again?

05:22.905 --> 05:26.242
No, my vacuum cleaner broke down,
so I have to buy a new one.

05:26.743 --> 05:28.995
Hey, that's still shopping.

05:29.078 --> 05:29.912
Is it?

05:29.996 --> 05:33.166
A lot of newlyweds frequent our store,
so the package discounts…

05:33.249 --> 05:34.500
Holy!

05:34.584 --> 05:36.044
…explained in detail.

05:36.127 --> 05:38.004
-Physical stores are our strength.
-Hello?

05:38.087 --> 05:40.131
-What is it?
-God, that scared me.

05:40.840 --> 05:42.425
It's the guy from my blind date.

05:43.092 --> 05:44.594
He works here. I remember now.

05:45.511 --> 05:49.182
What do I do?
I really need to buy a vacuum cleaner.

05:49.265 --> 05:51.559
Hey, that's great. Ask him for a discount.

05:51.642 --> 05:54.103
Are you insane?
I ghosted him after that day.

05:54.771 --> 05:56.397
Whatever! I'll call you back.

05:57.190 --> 06:00.109
So be prepared for that,
and the high-discount items…

06:00.193 --> 06:02.779
I'm running out of places to go
because of all the dates.

06:03.696 --> 06:05.198
Talk about karma.

06:06.908 --> 06:09.786
This is a place where any romance
you desire becomes reality.

06:10.703 --> 06:12.914
There are 900 themes just for you.

06:13.915 --> 06:17.293
So, who will you be dating today?

06:40.608 --> 06:41.442
Hello.

06:42.235 --> 06:43.569
-Doors opening.
-Hi.

06:53.621 --> 06:54.831
Doors closing.

07:16.227 --> 07:17.728
So I can get on with you.

07:42.295 --> 07:43.629
Hi.

07:43.713 --> 07:44.797
Hey, what's up?

08:05.485 --> 08:07.570
Come on, focus.

08:17.788 --> 08:18.623
What is it?

08:21.501 --> 08:23.503
Did you come here looking for me?

08:51.239 --> 08:52.865
I came here for this.

08:56.035 --> 08:57.370
I see. Right!

08:58.037 --> 08:59.539
You can take it.

09:00.081 --> 09:00.915
Okay.

09:04.585 --> 09:07.088
Drink this while you work.

09:08.839 --> 09:10.132
You got that for me?

09:10.716 --> 09:12.677
Yes. I had to come anyway, so…

09:15.346 --> 09:17.765
Come to think of it,
they are gone already.

09:19.433 --> 09:20.518
What do you mean?

09:21.852 --> 09:22.687
Your bangs.

09:24.605 --> 09:25.606
Looked good on you.

09:30.069 --> 09:30.903
Bye now.

09:31.779 --> 09:32.697
Okay.

10:03.394 --> 10:04.812
Stop being conscious of him.

10:04.895 --> 10:07.148
Don't show that you're losing composure!

10:07.231 --> 10:08.608
Get a grip!

10:25.249 --> 10:26.334
Ms. Seo.

10:29.462 --> 10:31.756
Here. This is yours.

10:32.965 --> 10:33.841
This is…

10:33.924 --> 10:35.468
I picked it up here in the lobby.

10:37.136 --> 10:40.056
I thought I had lost it. Thank you.

10:40.973 --> 10:41.974
That was

10:42.725 --> 10:43.934
my gift, by the way.

10:45.478 --> 10:48.648
I'm the one who put it in there
for the gift draw.

10:50.775 --> 10:53.527
You are the one who bought this? This?

10:54.320 --> 10:57.823
Yes. I bought this one for no reason
and put it in the box.

11:00.701 --> 11:03.287
-I didn't know that.
-Naturally. It was an anonymous draw.

11:06.207 --> 11:08.125
Anyway, thank you.

11:08.709 --> 11:10.378
Sure. See you tomorrow.

11:14.924 --> 11:15.925
Ms. Seo?

11:17.927 --> 11:20.262
Will you be putting it on again?

11:24.934 --> 11:26.102
Do whatever you'd like.

11:46.497 --> 11:47.748
This is driving me crazy.

11:52.628 --> 11:53.754
Good night.

11:55.631 --> 11:56.465
What was that?

12:04.974 --> 12:06.142
PRODUCER PARK
GOOD NIGHT

12:07.643 --> 12:10.813
Wait, did he just send me
a private message?

12:11.397 --> 12:12.857
This is crazy.

12:13.441 --> 12:14.275
Good night.

12:15.484 --> 12:18.863
Good night.

12:22.450 --> 12:24.201
This really is crazy.

12:32.293 --> 12:33.127
Huh?

12:34.044 --> 12:36.046
Why do I look so tired?

12:46.640 --> 12:47.892
None of this is working.

12:48.517 --> 12:50.728
Come to think of it,
they are gone already.

12:50.811 --> 12:51.812
Your bangs.

12:53.022 --> 12:54.273
Looked good on you.

13:15.002 --> 13:15.836
Gotcha.

13:27.431 --> 13:28.557
What?

13:28.641 --> 13:32.019
You have makeup on,
so why are you wearing a cap?

13:32.895 --> 13:33.729
What?

13:35.648 --> 13:37.316
I don't know. I just put it on.

13:40.528 --> 13:41.529
You worked all night?

13:42.112 --> 13:44.615
So you can reclaim the top spot for TMTK?

13:44.698 --> 13:46.283
Don't push yourself too hard.

13:46.367 --> 13:49.036
Ms. Seo, you look really exhausted.

13:49.119 --> 13:49.954
Yeah.

13:51.372 --> 13:52.373
I do?

13:52.456 --> 13:54.959
-Let's eat something nice today, okay?
-Love it.

13:55.042 --> 13:57.503
The platform and genre
will remain the same.

13:57.586 --> 14:00.589
Even for them, making a game
out of a series that's just started…

14:00.673 --> 14:02.842
I guess Kyeong-nam really is taking off.

14:02.925 --> 14:07.930
As if dethroning TMTK wasn't enough,
they're planning a game based on PlanC.

14:09.974 --> 14:12.268
A game? What kind of game?

14:12.768 --> 14:15.938
It seems he's in serious talks
with DU right now.

14:16.021 --> 14:19.358
What is it with everything
Park Kyeong-nam touches?

14:19.441 --> 14:22.862
At this rate, he's going to turn Hwany
into the undisputed champion.

14:22.945 --> 14:25.614
Look at Mr. Hwang
grinning from ear to ear.

14:25.698 --> 14:28.284
You know, Kyeong-nam scares me
more than anyone else.

14:28.367 --> 14:30.452
Such a solid guy, isn't he?

14:35.332 --> 14:36.250
Hey.

14:38.294 --> 14:39.128
Hello?

14:40.838 --> 14:42.172
Hello!

14:42.673 --> 14:43.507
Oh, yes?

14:43.591 --> 14:45.259
You are not listening to me.

14:45.342 --> 14:47.511
Why are you zoning out like that?

14:48.053 --> 14:49.263
Sorry. What did you say?

14:50.097 --> 14:53.350
I got a hand X-ray taken.

14:53.434 --> 14:57.187
The inflammation's so bad
that I have to eat with my left hand.

14:57.271 --> 14:59.273
But I can't use chopsticks with it, can I?

14:59.356 --> 15:00.441
Right.

15:01.650 --> 15:03.819
So stop ordering noodles for lunch.

15:06.155 --> 15:07.656
Okay. Understood.

15:19.126 --> 15:23.213
As if dethroning TMTK wasn't enough,
they're planning a game based on PlanC.

15:23.297 --> 15:26.717
At this rate, he's going to turn Hwany
into the undisputed champion.

15:27.676 --> 15:28.677
Ms. Yun!

15:29.553 --> 15:32.014
Don't you realize
how bad things are right now?

15:32.097 --> 15:34.224
We really need our heads in the game.

15:34.308 --> 15:36.727
The gap between PlanC and us
keeps widening.

15:36.810 --> 15:38.479
It's great that you're dating,

15:38.562 --> 15:41.482
but are you just going to give up on TMTK?

15:42.483 --> 15:44.693
Why are you being so serious
all of a sudden?

15:45.194 --> 15:46.820
All I did was text my boyfriend.

15:46.904 --> 15:48.238
How would men

15:48.322 --> 15:50.699
make any meaningful contribution
to our lives?

15:51.533 --> 15:52.993
-Huh?
-Think about it!

15:53.077 --> 15:55.955
Is it okay to let our relationships
affect our livelihoods?

15:56.038 --> 15:58.374
No, Ms. Yun. It's not okay.

15:59.291 --> 16:00.876
Where is this coming from?

16:01.961 --> 16:05.297
-Can't you just let me handle it myself?
-Absolutely not.

16:18.268 --> 16:19.770
You take the subway, right?

16:20.604 --> 16:23.565
I was thinking of taking the subway too.
We can go together.

16:39.039 --> 16:40.457
By the way,

16:40.541 --> 16:43.002
did you wear a cap
so you wouldn't look pretty for me?

16:43.085 --> 16:43.961
What?

16:45.170 --> 16:48.507
Oh, this? Nope, not at all.

16:49.758 --> 16:50.634
I thought maybe.

16:54.763 --> 16:58.017
Oh, I just remembered.
I have to take the bus today.

16:58.100 --> 16:59.727
Huh? You're taking the bus now?

16:59.810 --> 17:01.562
Yes. Have a safe trip home.

17:01.645 --> 17:02.521
Wait!

17:16.827 --> 17:18.203
But that bus is…

17:19.580 --> 17:22.541
Fasten your seatbelts.
We're approaching the highway.

17:23.208 --> 17:24.293
The highway?

17:25.210 --> 17:28.672
Wait, excuse me.
Where is this bus headed right now?

17:28.756 --> 17:29.590
Incheon.

17:30.174 --> 17:31.592
Incheon?

17:33.302 --> 17:35.721
You should sit back down. It's dangerous!

17:37.639 --> 17:39.224
He could have told me.

17:49.026 --> 17:50.444
The one who set us up told me

17:50.527 --> 17:54.239
that this will be your last blind date,
regardless of how it turns out.

17:55.532 --> 17:56.366
That's right.

17:56.450 --> 17:57.785
May I ask why?

18:00.454 --> 18:02.956
I've just grown really tired.

18:05.375 --> 18:06.293
I feel the same way.

18:06.376 --> 18:09.546
It's really hard to find someone you like.

18:09.630 --> 18:10.672
I agree.

18:10.756 --> 18:11.965
Do you have a type?

18:14.510 --> 18:15.844
I like

18:17.012 --> 18:19.264
men who are full of contradictions.

18:19.348 --> 18:22.476
-Full of contradictions?
-Yes.

18:23.310 --> 18:25.270
Someone who's neat but sexy,

18:25.354 --> 18:26.522
gentle but bad,

18:26.605 --> 18:28.107
and smart but sloppy.

18:28.190 --> 18:30.859
He should have a steady job
but be a free spirit,

18:30.943 --> 18:33.779
love books
without looking like a bookworm,

18:33.862 --> 18:36.907
have hard muscles but a soft heart,
and finally,

18:36.990 --> 18:39.701
be the kind of man
who says he'd never fall for me

18:39.785 --> 18:41.912
but loves me more than anyone else.

18:44.665 --> 18:46.083
-I see.
-Should I keep going?

18:47.459 --> 18:50.045
Excuse me. I need to take this call.

19:20.367 --> 19:21.201
Huh?

19:21.285 --> 19:22.661
The first song goes to

19:23.328 --> 19:27.499
the lady who asks for too much
but is beautiful enough to be forgiven.

19:29.001 --> 19:30.919
Is it over between you and that man?

19:32.963 --> 19:35.299
Well, yes, I suppose…

19:35.382 --> 19:36.967
I want you to forget about him.

19:48.270 --> 19:51.690
A story just for two of us

19:51.773 --> 19:55.611
The moon is shining on us

19:56.111 --> 20:00.073
My destiny, I'll hold you tight

20:02.326 --> 20:04.494
You're the one

20:04.578 --> 20:08.415
I sing this song for you

20:08.498 --> 20:12.836
I love you, I love you

20:12.920 --> 20:16.882
Now I confess my whole heart

20:17.549 --> 20:19.843
To you

20:23.555 --> 20:27.559
Congratulations, Ms. Lee Ji-yeon,
on meeting your first date!

20:46.286 --> 20:47.287
Awesome.

20:55.879 --> 21:00.425
The tree sure is bare this year,
with how busy Director Hwang is.

21:00.926 --> 21:05.013
I know. He used to gather us up
and decorate it, like it was a tradition.

21:05.097 --> 21:06.265
It's kind of sad.

21:07.266 --> 21:08.267
What do you mean?

21:10.102 --> 21:13.605
You know, a Christmas tree
is supposed to be all shiny and stuff.

21:14.940 --> 21:18.443
So the holidays have a way of making
even Seo Mi-rae sentimental.

21:18.944 --> 21:20.612
What are you all doing tomorrow?

21:20.696 --> 21:23.657
I'll probably watch dramas at home.

21:23.740 --> 21:26.827
I'm going on a staycation with friends.
What about you?

21:26.910 --> 21:29.579
-I'm going to church with my mom.
-I have it better.

21:30.247 --> 21:32.332
How about we go for a drink after work?

21:33.041 --> 21:35.460
Oh, the bars might be packed
since it's Christmas Eve.

21:35.544 --> 21:37.212
-I can't go.
-Why not?

21:37.296 --> 21:40.215
Christmas Eve or not,
today's just a TMTK update day for me.

21:42.551 --> 21:43.927
Oh well, let's go without her.

21:45.053 --> 21:45.929
Kyeong-nam.

21:47.264 --> 21:48.765
Are you also working late today?

21:49.474 --> 21:50.309
Yes.

21:51.893 --> 21:53.061
You poor things.

21:53.562 --> 21:58.150
Tell Hwany to take it easy.
He should pace himself while he's young.

22:02.738 --> 22:05.365
So, what about that place
we went to last time?

22:14.541 --> 22:18.295
Aren't I the only author on Fridays?
I always send in my work early.

22:20.088 --> 22:20.922
The thing is…

22:31.475 --> 22:32.934
Mr. Park.

22:35.103 --> 22:38.774
I guess Hwany is also late
with his submission today.

22:39.358 --> 22:40.192
No.

22:41.026 --> 22:41.860
Sorry?

22:42.569 --> 22:43.570
He already sent it.

22:47.324 --> 22:49.076
Then why are you still…

22:50.786 --> 22:52.329
Because I want to be here.

23:02.005 --> 23:04.591
Oh, I see. All right!

23:18.814 --> 23:19.648
YUN SONG

23:24.361 --> 23:25.195
UPLOAD COMPLETE

23:35.622 --> 23:36.456
What?

23:41.128 --> 23:41.962
What's going on?

23:43.255 --> 23:44.673
Is it a blackout?

24:29.801 --> 24:31.636
You said it made you sad, so…

24:36.224 --> 24:37.559
It's kind of sad.

24:38.768 --> 24:39.853
What do you mean?

24:39.936 --> 24:44.733
You know, a Christmas tree
is supposed to be all shiny and stuff.

25:21.269 --> 25:22.103
Ms. Seo.

25:25.315 --> 25:26.775
Are you taking the bus again?

25:29.444 --> 25:30.529
No.

25:40.539 --> 25:41.373
Thank you.

25:42.332 --> 25:45.585
I felt the Christmas spirit thanks to you.
It was nice.

25:46.962 --> 25:47.837
I enjoyed it.

25:55.554 --> 25:59.474
I heard about the PlanC game coming out.
Congratulations.

26:00.058 --> 26:01.977
It hasn't even been confirmed yet.

26:04.521 --> 26:06.982
How are you so good at everything you do?

26:08.149 --> 26:11.236
I get the impression that
you wouldn't have much to worry about.

26:11.778 --> 26:13.196
You do everything so easily.

26:14.281 --> 26:15.615
Did I come across that way?

26:16.116 --> 26:17.200
I'm not like that.

26:25.333 --> 26:26.835
LEE KYU-TAE SOLO EXHIBITION

26:26.918 --> 26:28.753
Do you know this artist?

26:30.088 --> 26:32.674
I buy their illustrated calendars
every year.

26:33.341 --> 26:37.095
Come to think of it, I get similar vibes
from their pieces as yours.

26:37.596 --> 26:39.848
I used to like this artist too.

26:41.474 --> 26:42.475
I see.

26:43.602 --> 26:45.520
The exhibition is going to end soon.

26:46.313 --> 26:47.147
It seems so.

26:50.525 --> 26:51.443
Wanna go with me?

26:56.531 --> 26:58.158
Did that come off too casually?

26:59.534 --> 27:01.453
Take your time and let me know.

27:12.339 --> 27:13.506
Aren't you hungry?

27:15.884 --> 27:17.886
It seemed like you were skipping dinner.

27:32.901 --> 27:36.988
By the way, why did you stop drawing?
You seemed to have a lot of talent.

27:39.282 --> 27:40.617
I didn't feel it anymore.

27:41.951 --> 27:42.786
Huh?

27:44.245 --> 27:46.665
Drawing used to mean everything to me,

27:47.165 --> 27:49.167
but suddenly it just felt different.

27:50.335 --> 27:52.003
I felt bad about changing,

27:52.504 --> 27:55.882
but at the same time, I was excited
to find something else I liked as much.

27:56.508 --> 27:57.342
That's why I quit.

28:00.595 --> 28:02.764
So did you find something
you liked as much?

28:03.348 --> 28:04.557
Turns out it wasn't easy

28:05.141 --> 28:08.728
to like something that much,
that consistently.

28:14.943 --> 28:16.611
-See you, then.
-Bye.

28:17.862 --> 28:19.155
Oh, wait.

28:33.044 --> 28:34.462
Read it later.

28:35.755 --> 28:36.589
Okay.

28:37.424 --> 28:38.258
Bye.

29:07.912 --> 29:10.665
Let's eat together next time.
Just the two of us.

29:19.591 --> 29:22.177
I wanted to tell you that I like you.

29:33.772 --> 29:35.190
Did you get home okay?

29:40.320 --> 29:41.571
YES

29:42.238 --> 29:43.072
GU YEONG-IL

29:43.156 --> 29:44.949
How much longer should I wait?

29:50.663 --> 29:52.665
I WANTED TO TELL YOU THAT I LIKE YOU

29:53.792 --> 29:56.628
How did I end up like this?

30:04.010 --> 30:04.844
You're here.

30:15.355 --> 30:17.273
-Hey--
-I got a bite.

30:25.448 --> 30:28.618
It seems they are only biting
whenever I try to say something.

30:29.828 --> 30:30.745
Seems so.

30:31.579 --> 30:32.413
How odd.

30:37.961 --> 30:38.795
What's wrong?

30:48.596 --> 30:50.431
I confessed my feelings to you,

30:50.515 --> 30:53.685
and now you're talking to me seriously
with a serious look.

30:53.768 --> 30:54.727
I'm scared.

30:58.398 --> 30:59.524
That I might say no?

31:00.984 --> 31:02.235
Are you going to?

31:15.456 --> 31:16.958
I can't catch a thing today.

31:19.210 --> 31:20.044
Let's go.

31:38.938 --> 31:39.939
Want me to draw you?

31:53.369 --> 31:54.370
Just act natural.

31:56.331 --> 31:57.165
Okay.

32:08.217 --> 32:09.052
Ms. Seo.

32:13.139 --> 32:14.474
I like you.

32:17.185 --> 32:18.353
From now on…

32:20.355 --> 32:21.481
can I do as I please?

32:33.368 --> 32:34.369
What's wrong?

32:41.042 --> 32:41.876
I'm sorry.

32:43.252 --> 32:44.337
What?

32:44.420 --> 32:45.338
Well,

32:46.339 --> 32:48.007
I won't be coming back here anymore.

32:51.761 --> 32:52.595
Why is that?

32:53.304 --> 32:55.682
You wouldn't understand
even if I told you,

32:56.474 --> 33:00.311
but the more I meet you,
the more I keep falling for someone.

33:01.646 --> 33:02.855
And that feels

33:03.898 --> 33:06.067
as though that person is having it easy.

33:08.736 --> 33:11.739
Do you mean that,
even when you're with me,

33:12.407 --> 33:14.742
another man keeps coming to mind?

33:20.748 --> 33:21.749
Do you like him?

33:27.922 --> 33:29.007
I don't know.

33:33.469 --> 33:35.555
How do you not know your own feelings?

33:35.638 --> 33:37.015
It's frustrating for me too.

33:37.640 --> 33:40.810
How about you?
Do you know what it is to like someone?

33:40.893 --> 33:43.229
You don't know what it's like
to truly like someone.

33:43.312 --> 33:44.522
I know.

33:46.315 --> 33:50.486
It's knowing you won't change,
even if the person you're with does.

33:52.989 --> 33:54.407
I never changed.

33:54.907 --> 33:56.242
Mi-rae.

33:56.325 --> 33:58.161
We all change.

33:58.745 --> 34:00.204
You've also changed.

34:06.002 --> 34:08.004
What you said about your drawings…

34:09.297 --> 34:12.133
Why are you so obsessed
with what changes and what doesn't?

34:13.259 --> 34:16.262
Is it such a big deal?
Why are you so obsessed with it?

34:17.388 --> 34:19.891
Could there be any other reason?

34:22.477 --> 34:24.562
That's the way I am. I can't help it.

34:26.939 --> 34:28.024
The way you are?

34:30.401 --> 34:32.403
There is a reason for everything.

34:33.696 --> 34:34.864
Because it was me

34:36.157 --> 34:37.408
who made you.

34:39.869 --> 34:40.995
Ms. Seo Mi-rae.

34:41.871 --> 34:43.831
I'm sure you know what I want…

34:44.415 --> 34:46.292
Even if you don't like me anymore…

34:46.959 --> 34:48.711
…and what I fear…

34:48.795 --> 34:50.463
…I won't ever change.

34:51.089 --> 34:52.924
…as well as I do.

34:53.007 --> 34:55.426
Because that's my way of liking someone.

34:56.052 --> 34:59.347
No. Perhaps even better than I do.

35:00.181 --> 35:01.265
Did he tell you

35:02.016 --> 35:03.017
that he won't change?

35:11.192 --> 35:12.527
I didn't feel it anymore.

35:12.610 --> 35:14.237
Turns out it wasn't easy

35:14.320 --> 35:18.116
to like something that much,
that consistently.

35:28.876 --> 35:30.628
When his feelings for you change,

35:31.671 --> 35:33.256
are you certain you won't get hurt?

35:40.930 --> 35:42.098
As for me…

35:44.433 --> 35:46.435
I won't ever hurt you.

35:48.604 --> 35:49.438
So,

35:51.315 --> 35:52.400
don't go.

36:14.005 --> 36:15.089
Ms. Seo.

36:22.013 --> 36:24.223
-It's the final evaluations already.
-So it is.

36:24.307 --> 36:27.185
Fantasy was super competitive this year.
How about you guys?

36:27.268 --> 36:29.478
Ours was intense as well.

36:29.562 --> 36:32.899
Kyeong-nam and Mi-rae would keep going
back and forth about who was right.

36:32.982 --> 36:33.816
All right.

36:33.900 --> 36:36.861
Mr. Hwang can't make it today,
so let's get started.

36:36.944 --> 36:37.778
-Okay.
-Sure.

36:42.408 --> 36:46.245
This one's well-balanced,
but isn't it a bit too old-fashioned?

36:46.329 --> 36:49.874
A bit lacking in that regard,
but at least it's a safe choice.

36:51.417 --> 36:57.256
It's not bad, but it's not great.
It's smooth, but it lacks an edge.

36:59.217 --> 37:00.801
Put it on hold for now?

37:02.053 --> 37:02.970
Okay.

37:03.054 --> 37:04.931
Who needs to use the restroom?

37:05.014 --> 37:06.724
-I do.
-Me too.

37:22.073 --> 37:24.825
I think every piece needs to pack a punch.

37:24.909 --> 37:26.160
The references…

37:26.244 --> 37:28.496
Oh, I left my phone behind.

37:28.579 --> 37:29.664
Make me a coffee.

37:34.168 --> 37:36.003
Go ahead. I'm not going to use it.

37:36.087 --> 37:37.088
Ms. Seo.

37:40.466 --> 37:41.384
Are you sick?

37:44.470 --> 37:45.513
No.

37:47.056 --> 37:49.058
You just don't look too good.

37:53.729 --> 37:55.064
Anyway, so…

37:58.109 --> 38:03.072
What you said about doing as you please,

38:03.572 --> 38:05.950
I get what you meant by that now.

38:06.867 --> 38:09.120
But whatever it is,

38:09.954 --> 38:13.040
I'd appreciate it
if you could stop doing it at work.

38:16.585 --> 38:18.504
At work?

38:22.925 --> 38:24.510
I didn't phrase that correctly.

38:26.053 --> 38:29.390
Just stop doing it altogether,
wherever it may be.

38:31.517 --> 38:32.935
Please.

38:40.234 --> 38:43.070
Huh? I said I wanted some coffee.

38:46.866 --> 38:47.867
You want one, yeah?

38:57.251 --> 38:58.919
-Move on to the next piece?
-Okay.

38:59.503 --> 39:02.048
A-606. Crimson-Eyed Elena.

39:02.631 --> 39:06.218
What do we have here?
I love the style. Who picked this one?

39:08.304 --> 39:11.724
Actually, we had mixed opinions
about this piece.

39:12.308 --> 39:13.142
So…

39:18.397 --> 39:19.815
I'm the one who approved of it.

39:20.316 --> 39:25.571
Kyeong-nam and Mi-rae
never saw eye to eye on this one.

39:28.741 --> 39:31.994
I think this piece is fully qualified.

39:32.661 --> 39:34.663
And Mi-rae? Are you still against it?

39:36.874 --> 39:37.708
Yes.

39:38.626 --> 39:39.460
I don't like it.

39:41.587 --> 39:43.464
It is a little rough around the edges.

39:44.673 --> 39:46.592
-What don't you like exactly?
-Huh?

39:50.763 --> 39:53.015
I think I've already told you
several times.

39:53.099 --> 39:55.351
This is a contest for rookies.

39:55.434 --> 39:59.855
Director Hwang told us to focus
on the potential, and I saw the potential.

40:01.190 --> 40:02.775
Well, I didn't see it.

40:02.858 --> 40:04.860
You almost changed your mind at one point.

40:09.073 --> 40:10.825
From start to finish, did you really

40:12.284 --> 40:13.619
hate all of it?

40:17.081 --> 40:17.915
Yes.

40:21.252 --> 40:22.920
And I don't think…

40:25.798 --> 40:27.216
that will ever change.

40:35.641 --> 40:37.893
Yes! Now that's what I call a meeting!

40:38.394 --> 40:42.314
Why don't we call it for today
and finish talking about it tomorrow?

40:42.398 --> 40:44.525
-Sounds good.
-Good work, everyone.

40:44.608 --> 40:46.110
We worked too hard today, huh?

40:46.610 --> 40:47.695
-Good work.
-I'm tired.

40:47.778 --> 40:48.779
Let's go.

40:51.365 --> 40:53.492
Good work, everyone.

41:42.416 --> 41:44.168
I just remembered

41:45.169 --> 41:49.048
why I was so adamant
about not dating anyone.

41:50.424 --> 41:51.592
But

41:52.218 --> 41:56.555
seeing how scared I am
of Kyeong-nam changing…

42:03.562 --> 42:07.441
I guess he really was the person
I truly liked.

42:09.693 --> 42:14.406
I used to think that you were the reason
Kyeong-nam made my heart race,

42:15.449 --> 42:17.034
but I think I must have…

42:20.412 --> 42:21.747
actually liked him.

42:24.208 --> 42:25.876
That's why I held onto you.

42:28.671 --> 42:30.214
I didn't wanna see you suffer.

42:31.632 --> 42:33.175
It's bound to end someday,

42:34.593 --> 42:36.595
and you will have to deal with it alone.

42:37.096 --> 42:38.931
Ending up alone again,

42:40.224 --> 42:41.642
you hate it more than anything.

42:43.227 --> 42:44.812
I wanted to forget.

42:44.895 --> 42:46.272
Are you okay?

42:52.152 --> 42:55.406
Goodness, you fool.

42:59.159 --> 43:02.538
MI-RAE, SE-JUNE

43:39.033 --> 43:40.868
Here's the shrimp ball.

43:42.411 --> 43:44.663
-You're not gonna let me have that?
-No way.

43:44.747 --> 43:46.915
-You're the best.
-Thank you, ma'am.

43:47.750 --> 43:49.084
-Here.
-Okay.

43:49.168 --> 43:50.836
Your legs are very tight, ma'am.

43:50.919 --> 43:52.421
Your hair's so damaged, ma'am.

43:52.504 --> 43:54.006
Easy. Do it from a distance.

43:54.089 --> 43:55.174
Right. I'm sorry.

43:55.257 --> 43:56.091
Look.

43:57.134 --> 43:58.636
It's hilarious. Look.

44:02.473 --> 44:05.893
What had always been part of a pair
was suddenly alone.

44:07.394 --> 44:10.648
When it dawned upon me
that he was never coming back,

44:11.565 --> 44:13.317
it hurt so much.

44:18.572 --> 44:19.907
And you're afraid

44:20.532 --> 44:22.201
that it might happen.

44:27.498 --> 44:29.249
The man I created…

44:31.335 --> 44:34.505
keeps weakening my resolve,
over and over again.

44:38.759 --> 44:39.843
You did well.

44:40.969 --> 44:42.137
It's the right thing.

45:00.280 --> 45:02.783
I buy their illustrated calendars
every year.

45:03.784 --> 45:05.035
Wanna go with me?

45:30.853 --> 45:35.023
If it's going to end anyway,
it's better not to start it at all.

45:49.830 --> 45:52.207
Jeong-hyu wrapped up this episode nicely.

45:52.291 --> 45:54.251
When should I pay off the setups?

45:57.421 --> 45:59.131
Hold on. I need to take this call.

46:00.340 --> 46:01.300
Hey, Mom.

46:12.686 --> 46:15.355
I'm sorry, but I guess…

46:15.439 --> 46:19.109
Three cups of coffee, three treats.
What are you getting at here?

46:19.610 --> 46:21.695
Well, since there are three of us--

46:21.779 --> 46:23.864
Again with the three!

46:23.947 --> 46:26.575
Are you putting it out there
that TMTK is in third place?

46:26.658 --> 46:28.285
…I'm not brave enough.

47:05.322 --> 47:07.658
Anyway, you all worked so hard last year.

47:07.741 --> 47:10.160
-Here's to us!
-Great work, everyone!

47:10.828 --> 47:13.163
It's time for me to share some good news.

47:13.247 --> 47:16.875
Oh well, I guess for you guys,
it might come across as somewhat sad news.

47:16.959 --> 47:19.253
Starting this year,

47:19.336 --> 47:23.215
we have decided to really jump into
the American webtoon platform race.

47:23.298 --> 47:26.969
And that's why we are going to send
Korea's finest over there.

47:27.886 --> 47:28.720
Who might that be?

47:33.517 --> 47:34.351
It's me.

47:37.813 --> 47:40.065
I'm leaving. For the States. As the CEO.

47:41.358 --> 47:43.902
Director Hwang! No, CEO Hwang!

47:43.986 --> 47:45.404
-Oh please!
-Congratulations!

47:45.487 --> 47:49.992
Come on, how are we supposed to manage
if you just leave us like that?

47:50.075 --> 47:53.871
Hey now, I still have a few months left.
Don't be like that.

47:53.954 --> 47:58.083
I'm a bit torn up
about having to leave you guys behind.

47:58.166 --> 48:00.419
We should start preparing
a farewell party, right?

48:00.502 --> 48:03.839
Of course.
A grand celebration that befits him.

48:03.922 --> 48:04.756
True.

48:04.840 --> 48:07.259
Hey! That was on me!

48:07.342 --> 48:08.927
-Thanks!
-I told you I was buying.

48:09.011 --> 48:10.429
-You're the best!
-Thank you.

48:10.512 --> 48:12.264
I'm spending it all before I leave!

48:12.347 --> 48:14.099
-Let's join him today.
-Director Hwang!

48:15.475 --> 48:16.643
-Where to?
-Let's go!

48:16.727 --> 48:19.897
-Awesome!
-Where is she going? Hey!

48:21.565 --> 48:22.733
It's so cold.

48:22.816 --> 48:24.026
Seo Mi-rae!

48:25.027 --> 48:26.361
Let's share this one.

48:26.445 --> 48:27.362
Okay.

48:30.449 --> 48:31.617
Thanks.

48:44.171 --> 48:47.174
I'll get out first, then you,
and Kyeong-nam will get out last.

48:56.391 --> 48:57.726
Rest up, guys.

48:57.809 --> 48:59.686
-Thank you, sir.
-Sure. Have a good night.

49:06.318 --> 49:07.319
Weather update.

49:07.402 --> 49:11.615
Snowfall centered over the central region
has continued since this evening.

49:11.698 --> 49:14.826
It is falling at a rate
of about 1 cm per hour in Seoul,

49:14.910 --> 49:17.871
Northern Gyeonggi-do,
and Yeongseo, Gangwon-do.

49:17.955 --> 49:19.665
Around the city…

49:19.748 --> 49:21.750
Sir, you can drop me off here.

49:21.833 --> 49:22.668
Sure thing.

49:29.341 --> 49:32.344
I'll be going now. Happy holidays.

49:32.427 --> 49:33.512
Wait.

49:37.140 --> 49:38.809
Take this. It's snowing a lot.

49:40.268 --> 49:42.688
It's fine.
We're right in front of my place.

49:42.771 --> 49:44.606
Goodbye, then.

50:02.499 --> 50:03.583
Ms. Seo!

50:13.010 --> 50:14.219
Take this.

50:17.597 --> 50:18.432
But I…

50:19.599 --> 50:20.517
I said I was okay.

50:23.145 --> 50:24.938
You won't accept anything from me?

50:27.274 --> 50:28.108
What?

50:35.073 --> 50:36.324
Just use it.

50:44.750 --> 50:48.462
How are you going to get home?
You can't hail a cab right now.

50:51.048 --> 50:52.299
I'll manage.

50:53.133 --> 50:53.967
Hey.

50:54.801 --> 50:55.635
Mr. Park.

50:56.511 --> 51:00.474
Take this back.
I don't want to accept this.

51:03.560 --> 51:05.604
I just don't want you to get snowed on.

51:06.855 --> 51:08.857
Does a small favor really bother you?

51:12.569 --> 51:13.737
Did I ever

51:14.446 --> 51:16.114
ask you to like me?

51:21.411 --> 51:22.412
Don't you think

51:24.039 --> 51:25.749
you're being too inconsiderate?

51:28.460 --> 51:30.670
Do you only care about your own feelings?

51:33.256 --> 51:35.258
I mean, have you considered

51:36.510 --> 51:38.011
how I might feel about things?

51:41.056 --> 51:42.224
This is

51:43.058 --> 51:44.226
hard for me too.

51:45.644 --> 51:49.648
I hate myself for how much I sway
every time you stir my heart.

51:50.273 --> 51:51.691
This is difficult for me too.

51:53.819 --> 51:56.154
But so what if I get swayed?

51:57.697 --> 51:59.116
What are you suggesting?

52:00.992 --> 52:02.494
That we start dating right away?

52:05.413 --> 52:06.706
Why can't we?

52:10.210 --> 52:11.545
Are you being serious?

52:11.628 --> 52:13.672
What are you so afraid of?

52:15.048 --> 52:17.134
We haven't even begun yet.

52:17.217 --> 52:18.885
If there's a beginning…

52:21.012 --> 52:22.639
there will be an end too.

52:22.722 --> 52:23.890
I…

52:26.309 --> 52:28.145
don't think about the end right now.

52:31.064 --> 52:34.568
For now, sure,
but you'll change eventually.

52:34.651 --> 52:36.486
Do you hate change that much?

52:37.612 --> 52:40.448
Is change really that bad?

52:43.326 --> 52:44.411
Ever since…

52:47.247 --> 52:48.915
I fell for you, Seo Mi-rae…

52:51.293 --> 52:52.460
I've changed.

57:37.662 --> 57:42.667
Subtitle translation by: Daham Yoon
